 <p class="p" xmlns="">‘It is worrying that rivers are now drying up so early. This has serious consequences because we need water for domestic use, livestock and irrigation. It has become a norm in our community that from June through November we struggle for water and often queue for water at the local bore hole.’ (Female, 65, farmer)</p>
